WEBVTT

00:24.658 --> 00:27.695
LYSANDER,
YOU CAN'T DO THIS!
WHAT ABOUT THE CURSE?

00:27.761 --> 00:29.263
THE CENTAUR?

00:29.330 --> 00:32.166
PLEASE. YOU'RE TOO
SMART TO BELIEVE
THAT FOOLISH FABLE.

00:32.233 --> 00:35.636
I'M ALSO TOO SMART
TO FOLLOW YOU ANY FURTHER.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.271
SUIT YOURSELF.

00:49.717 --> 00:51.119
[SPLASHING IN WATER]

00:52.720 --> 00:55.323
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

01:02.029 --> 01:04.064
[GROWLING]

01:07.268 --> 01:09.470
OH, NO--PLEASE!

01:09.537 --> 01:11.139
NO! NO!

01:13.441 --> 01:14.475
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:14.542 --> 01:16.444
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:16.510 --> 01:19.213
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:19.280 --> 01:20.481
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:20.548 --> 01:22.350
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:22.416 --> 01:25.119
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:25.186 --> 01:26.420
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:26.487 --> 01:28.156
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

01:28.222 --> 01:30.924
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:30.991 --> 01:32.393
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:32.460 --> 01:34.061
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:34.128 --> 01:36.797
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:38.566 --> 01:40.301
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:40.368 --> 01:44.538
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

01:44.605 --> 01:49.076
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

01:49.143 --> 01:50.444
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:50.511 --> 01:51.879
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:51.945 --> 01:54.882
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:54.948 --> 01:56.384
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:56.450 --> 01:57.918
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:57.985 --> 02:00.721
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

02:00.788 --> 02:02.223
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:02.290 --> 02:03.791
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:03.857 --> 02:06.460
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

02:06.527 --> 02:10.063
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:10.130 --> 02:12.700
* WHAT'S NEW,
SCOOBY-DOO? *

02:16.504 --> 02:19.540
THE BIRTHPLACE OF DEMOCRACY
AND EPIC LITERATURE

02:19.607 --> 02:20.774
AND MATHEMATICS!

02:20.841 --> 02:23.076
AND HUMMUS
AND FETA CHEESE,

02:23.143 --> 02:24.912
AND GREEK SALAD.

02:24.978 --> 02:27.581
[SPEAKING GREEK]

02:28.549 --> 02:30.418
I'M NOT SURE
I WANT TO KNOW,

02:30.484 --> 02:32.620
BUT...
WHAT'S HE SAYING?

02:32.686 --> 02:34.655
WELL, LET ME CONSULT
MY TRUSTY PHRASE BOOK.

02:34.722 --> 02:36.757
LET'S SEE...

02:36.824 --> 02:37.991
IT SAYS HERE THAT...

02:38.058 --> 02:40.294
HE'S GOT BIG LEAVES
IN HIS BOOTS.

02:40.361 --> 02:42.230
NO, THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

02:42.296 --> 02:45.132
[SPEAKING GREEK]

02:45.199 --> 02:47.568
ZTNATHANATHAS. YEAH.

02:47.635 --> 02:51.739
OH! HE'S WONDERING
IF HE CAN BORROW
OUR PACK MULE.

02:51.805 --> 02:54.208
NO. OH, HERE IT IS!

02:54.275 --> 02:57.845
HE'S SAYING "THE GREEK GODS
SHALL BRING CHAOS
INTO YOUR LIVES."

02:57.911 --> 03:01.114
MAN, I READ THE BROCHURE,
AND NOWHERE DID IT TALK ABOUT

03:01.181 --> 03:04.051
GETTING CURSED
BY THE LOCAL LOONIES!

03:04.117 --> 03:06.420
[SPEAKING GREEK]

03:13.361 --> 03:15.329
THIS MINIATURE PARTHENON
SURE WILL LOOK GOOD

03:15.396 --> 03:18.165
IN MY THERMOMETERS
FROM AROUND THE WORLD
COLLECTION.

03:18.232 --> 03:19.667
CLASSY.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.704
THIS THING IS DANGEROUS.

03:23.771 --> 03:26.139
YOU KNOW THE CENTAUR
WILL CONTINUE TO ATTACK US

03:26.206 --> 03:27.541
AS LONG AS WE HAVE IT!

03:27.608 --> 03:29.943
IT'S MINE!
GIVE IT BACK!

03:36.016 --> 03:38.051
HEY, SCOOB,
CHECK IT OUT!

03:38.118 --> 03:39.920
AH, WISE CHOICE,
MY FRIEND.

03:39.987 --> 03:40.988
WISE CHOICE.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.291
THAT IS ONE
POWERFUL AMULET.

03:43.357 --> 03:45.293
POWERFUL? HA HA HA!

03:45.359 --> 03:47.295
LIKE, TELL ME IT KEEPS
MONSTERS AWAY,

03:47.361 --> 03:48.562
AND YOU'VE GOT A SALE.

03:48.629 --> 03:50.431
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT IT DOES!

03:50.498 --> 03:52.700
IT IS AN ANCIENT
GREEK MEDALLION

03:52.766 --> 03:55.403
THAT KEEPS AWAY
ALL KINDS OF MONSTERS!

03:55.469 --> 03:58.071
WHOA! IMAGINE THE ODDS,
EH, SCOOB?

03:58.138 --> 03:59.640
OH, BOY.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.751
IT'S NOT HERE!

04:10.818 --> 04:11.619
WHERE IS IT?

04:11.685 --> 04:14.522
THE GOLD ONE...
WITH THE RUBY!

04:14.588 --> 04:16.957
HA. IT IS JUST
A WORTHLESS TRINKET.

04:17.024 --> 04:18.426
I HAVE MANY MORE.

04:18.492 --> 04:20.428
THAT WAS NO TRINKET!
IT WAS REAL!

04:20.494 --> 04:21.595
NOW, WHERE IS IT?

04:21.662 --> 04:25.433
BUT...I--I SOLD IT...
TO HIM!

04:29.002 --> 04:30.704
FRIENDS, COUNTRYMEN...

04:30.771 --> 04:33.140
OH, NO!
MY PURSE IS MISSING!

04:33.206 --> 04:35.008
DON'T YOU HAVE
A BUNCH OF THEM?

04:35.075 --> 04:38.479
7 PURPLE, 3 GREEN,
A TOTALLY AWESOME
BURGUNDY.

04:38.546 --> 04:40.848
BUT THAT WAS
THE ONLY ONE
I BROUGHT TO GREECE!

04:40.914 --> 04:43.250
SO, LIKE, WHERE'S
THE CONCESSION GUY?

04:43.317 --> 04:45.619
SHAGGY,
IT'S NOT A BALL PARK.

04:45.686 --> 04:47.955
THIS IS THE ANCIENT
THEATER OF DIONYSUS

04:48.021 --> 04:50.891
WHERE THE GREEK TRAGEDIES
WERE ORIGINALLY PERFORMED.

04:50.958 --> 04:52.025
THEY DON'T HAVE--

04:52.092 --> 04:53.226
FETA CHEESE
ON A STICK!

04:53.293 --> 04:54.528
GET YOUR FETA RIGHT HERE!

04:54.595 --> 04:57.064
WOW. DOES HE HAVE
ANY BAKLAVA?

05:01.101 --> 05:02.503
LIKE, MAN, SCOOB,

05:02.570 --> 05:04.505
THOSE ANCIENT GREEKS
WERE WAY AHEAD
OF THEIR TIME!

05:04.572 --> 05:06.173
THIS IS BETTER THAN
THE MOVIES!

05:06.239 --> 05:07.575
[ROARING]

05:07.641 --> 05:10.878
WHO KNEW
THEY HAD SUCH GREAT
SPECIAL EFFECTS?

05:10.944 --> 05:13.146
RRRRRR!

05:13.213 --> 05:14.948
TALK ABOUT
INTERACTIVE!

05:15.015 --> 05:17.250
THIS
MYTHOLOGICAL BEAST
LOOKS SO REAL!

05:17.317 --> 05:20.120
IT'S CALLED A CENTAUR
AND, UH...

05:20.187 --> 05:21.589
I THINK IT IS REAL.

05:21.655 --> 05:22.923
WHAT MAKES YOU
SAY THAT?

05:22.990 --> 05:24.958
AAH!
AAH!

05:25.025 --> 05:26.259
[ROAR]

05:26.326 --> 05:28.362
WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

05:28.429 --> 05:30.431
HOW TO SAY RUN
IN GREEK!

05:30.498 --> 05:32.533
LIKE, THANKS, FRED.
BUT THAT'S ONE PHRASE

05:32.600 --> 05:34.568
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
TRANSLATE!

05:37.137 --> 05:39.106
Shaggy: GANGWAY!

05:51.284 --> 05:53.153
JUST HANG IN THERE,
GUYS!

05:53.220 --> 05:55.789
LIKE, EASY FOR HIM
TO SAY.

05:58.526 --> 06:02.496
HEY. I ALMOST FORGOT
ABOUT MY LUCKY AMULET.

06:10.738 --> 06:13.073
WOW! THIS AMULET
REALLY WORKS, SCOOB.

06:13.140 --> 06:15.175
IT SAVED US
FROM THE MONSTER!

06:15.242 --> 06:16.877
OH, RAGGY!

06:16.944 --> 06:18.679
BETTER KEEP THIS THING
IN A SAFE PLACE.

06:18.746 --> 06:21.415
WELL, GANG,
IT LOOKS LIKE...
[PANTING]

06:21.482 --> 06:24.618
LOOKS LIKE WE'VE GOT
A MYSTERY...
ON OUR HANDS.

06:24.685 --> 06:26.854
MAN, I GOTTA START
WORKING OUT.

06:26.920 --> 06:30.424
MYSTERY? THAT OLD GUY
AT THE AIRPORT
PUT A CURSE ON US.

06:30.491 --> 06:33.160
LIKE, WHAT'S THE MYSTERY?
WE'RE CURSED!

06:39.232 --> 06:40.868
I DON'T BELIEVE
IN CURSES.

06:40.934 --> 06:44.104
I SAY IT'S TIME
WE DO A LITTLE
RESEARCH...

06:44.171 --> 06:46.674
AT THE HISTORICAL
SOCIETY OF ATHENS.

06:46.740 --> 06:49.577
IT HAS THE BODY
OF A HORSE BUT
THE HEAD OF A MAN.

06:49.643 --> 06:51.745
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN HELP US,
MAJOR PORTSMITH?

06:51.812 --> 06:54.047
IT'S PORTSMOUTH,
AND OF COURSE I CAN.

06:54.114 --> 06:57.184
THERE'S A VERY
RATIONAL EXPLANATION
FOR ALL THIS.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.786
SEE? I TOLD YOU.

06:58.852 --> 07:02.189
THE MYTHOLOGICAL
CREATURES ARE REAL!

07:02.255 --> 07:03.356
EXCUSE ME?
WHAT?

07:03.423 --> 07:05.092
I'VE SPENT
MY ENTIRE CAREER

07:05.158 --> 07:07.628
TRYING TO PROVE
THE MYTHS ARE REAL.

07:07.695 --> 07:10.631
NO ONE WOULD BELIEVE ME.
NO ONE!

07:10.698 --> 07:13.200
BUT NOW
THAT THERE'S BEEN
AN ACTUAL SIGHTING...

07:13.266 --> 07:15.368
OH HO! THANK YOU, KIDS.

07:15.435 --> 07:16.236
THANK YOU!

07:16.303 --> 07:17.370
THIS IS WHAT I HAVE

07:17.437 --> 07:20.474
BEEN WAITING
MY WHOLE LIFE TO HEAR!

07:20.541 --> 07:22.510
DOES HE EVEN WORK
HERE?

07:24.845 --> 07:27.214
WE HAVE TO START ASKING
FOR CREDENTIALS.

07:31.685 --> 07:32.920
[YELLING IN GREEK]

07:34.988 --> 07:37.558
ISN'T THAT
THE SCARY LOOKING GUY
FROM THE AIRPORT?

07:37.625 --> 07:39.627
HE'S BACK
TO CURSE US AGAIN!

07:39.693 --> 07:42.095
WELL, YOU HAVE TO ADMIRE
HIS DEDICATION.

07:48.702 --> 07:50.704
[YELLING IN GREEK]

07:57.678 --> 08:00.213
SERIOUSLY...
A GYM MEMBERSHIP.

08:00.280 --> 08:01.348
FOR CHRISTMAS.

08:01.414 --> 08:02.683
WRITE IT DOWN.

08:02.750 --> 08:05.919
WOW! THE ANCIENT
ACROPOLIS!

08:05.986 --> 08:07.621
THIS IS AMAZING!

08:15.428 --> 08:17.030
HEY, SCOOB,
CHECK IT OUT.

08:17.097 --> 08:18.365
PFFT!

08:18.431 --> 08:19.533
[GIGGLING]

08:19.600 --> 08:21.669
HA HA HA HA!

08:21.735 --> 08:23.971
NOT SO TOUGH
WHEN YOU'RE MADE
OUT OF STONE, ARE YA?

08:24.037 --> 08:26.306
LIKE, NOT NOW, SCOOB.
I'M ON A ROLL!

08:26.373 --> 08:28.842
[WHIMPERING]

08:28.909 --> 08:30.544
OH, HI.

08:48.328 --> 08:50.831
[ROAR]

08:58.271 --> 09:00.240
HA HA HA HA!

09:14.722 --> 09:17.024
LIKE, THANKS, MAN.
YOU'RE A LIFESAVER.

09:17.090 --> 09:19.760
NOW GIVE TO ME
WHAT I CAME FOR!

09:40.614 --> 09:42.215
[FERRY HORN BLOWING]

09:44.317 --> 09:45.986
ALRIGHT!
OH!

09:53.627 --> 09:54.895
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

09:54.962 --> 09:57.698
OH, NO!
FIRST THE SCARY CENTAUR,

09:57.765 --> 10:00.701
NOW THE OLD MANIAC
MOPED GUY!

10:03.570 --> 10:05.873
[YELLING]

10:09.576 --> 10:10.377
UH-UH.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.611
DON'T WORRY, GANG.

10:11.679 --> 10:14.381
I'LL GET US
FIRST-CLASS ACCOMMODATIONS.

10:15.548 --> 10:17.517
[BAA]

10:17.584 --> 10:21.221
LOOKS LIKE THIS PLACE
COULD USE A DAPHNE DO-OVER.

10:21.288 --> 10:24.291
SOME NEW DRAPES,
SOME THROW PILLOWS...

10:24.357 --> 10:26.459
SOME DEODORIZER.

10:26.526 --> 10:29.262
OH! I FORGOT!
I LOST MY PURSE!

10:29.329 --> 10:31.631
SORRY, GUYS.

10:42.575 --> 10:43.977
[BLEATS]

11:00.393 --> 11:02.029
[CHOMP]
[MUFFLED YELL]

11:10.570 --> 11:11.504
[YELLS] OW!

11:11.571 --> 11:13.774
[ALL MOANING]

11:16.844 --> 11:18.445
Velma: IT'S
THE ISLAND OF CRETE.

11:18.511 --> 11:21.749
ANYPLACE
THAT'S CENTAUR-FREE
SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.

11:21.815 --> 11:23.583
HEY! ISN'T THAT
MAJOR PORTSMITH

11:23.650 --> 11:25.518
FROM THE HISTORICAL
SOCIETY?

11:25.585 --> 11:26.954
IT'S PORTSMOUTH.

11:27.020 --> 11:29.790
LET'S FOLLOW HIM
AND FIND OUT WHAT
HE'S UP TO.

11:30.958 --> 11:33.393
GREAT. NOW WHAT
ARE WE GOING TO DO?

11:33.460 --> 11:36.864
JUST LEAVE THAT TO ME
AND MY TRUSTY PHRASE BOOK.

11:38.932 --> 11:41.301
ONE OF US HAS TO
STEAL THAT BOOK.

11:41.368 --> 11:42.970
I'M SERIOUS.

11:54.214 --> 11:54.982
HUH?

11:55.048 --> 11:57.450
ZOINKS!
IT'S THE CENTAUR!

12:08.628 --> 12:10.263
AH!

12:16.770 --> 12:18.638
WOW!
THAT WAS AMAZING!

12:18.705 --> 12:21.541
IT SURE WAS.
WE TRAPPED THE CENTAUR.

12:21.608 --> 12:23.576
I MEANT THE BRAKES
ON THIS CAR!

12:23.643 --> 12:24.812
KIDS!

12:24.878 --> 12:26.479
OH, KIDS,
THERE YOU ARE.

12:26.546 --> 12:29.082
HAVE YOU SEEN IT?
HAVE YOU SEEN
THE CENTAUR?

12:29.149 --> 12:31.985
WE SURE HAVE.
IT'S TRAPPED
RIGHT OVER THERE!

12:32.052 --> 12:35.122
INSIDE
THE MINOTAUR'S MAZE.
HA HA HA HA!

12:35.188 --> 12:36.589
GOOD SHOW!

12:36.656 --> 12:39.927
THE BEAST WILL NEVER
GET OUT OF THAT
TWISTING, TURNING TRAP.

12:39.993 --> 12:41.628
SINCE WE'VE
TRAPPED THE CENTAUR,

12:41.694 --> 12:43.563
I GUESS OUR WORK HERE
IS DONE, SCOOB.

12:43.630 --> 12:46.599
TIME TO GO BACK
TO ATHENS AND SAMPLE
SOME HUMMUS.

12:46.666 --> 12:48.435
REAH. HUMMUS.

12:48.501 --> 12:49.837
NOT SO FAST,
YOU TWO.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.571
WE NEED SOMEONE
TO GO INTO THE MAZE

12:51.638 --> 12:53.473
AND FLUSH OUT
THAT CENTAUR.

12:53.540 --> 12:55.075
HA HA HA!
LIKE, NO WAY.

12:55.142 --> 12:56.877
SCOOB AND I
ARE NOT INTERESTED.

12:56.944 --> 12:59.112
UH-UH. NO WAY.

12:59.179 --> 13:01.648
OH, YEAH? WOULD YOU
DO IT FOR SOME--

13:01.714 --> 13:04.617
OOPS! THE SCOOBY SNAX
ARE IN MY PURSE.

13:04.684 --> 13:07.687
DO YOU GUYS TAKE IOUs?

13:07.754 --> 13:09.356
DON'T WORRY,
SCOOB, OLD BUDDY.

13:09.422 --> 13:12.192
I TIED A PIECE OF STRING
AT THE ENTRANCE
TO THE MAZE.

13:12.259 --> 13:15.162
THAT WAY,
WHEN WE WANT OUT,
WE JUST FOLLOW IT BACK,

13:15.228 --> 13:16.763
SEE?

13:16.830 --> 13:18.665
LIKE...[GULP] HA HA!

13:18.731 --> 13:20.533
THE STRING'S
BEEN CUT.

13:20.600 --> 13:21.634
UH-OH.

13:21.701 --> 13:23.370
WELL...DOES THAT
WHITE STONE

13:23.436 --> 13:26.473
TOTALLY PLAIN WALL
LOOK FAMILIAR TO YOU?

13:26.539 --> 13:27.640
NO.

13:27.707 --> 13:29.576
YEAH.
LIKE, ME NEITHER.

13:29.642 --> 13:31.144
WE'RE LOST!
WE'RE LOST, SCOOB,

13:31.211 --> 13:33.513
LOST IN
THE MINOTAUR'S MAZE!

13:36.149 --> 13:38.085
LIKE, THANKS, MAN.

13:42.589 --> 13:43.823
THE CENTAUR!

13:43.891 --> 13:45.425
RUN FOR IT!

13:57.170 --> 14:00.974
OH, NO! IT SOUNDS LIKE
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY
ARE IN TROUBLE.

14:08.615 --> 14:11.952
IT MAKES SENSE
THAT WE'RE IN
ANCIENT GREECE, SCOOB.

14:12.019 --> 14:14.554
'CAUSE WE ARE ABOUT
TO BE HISTORY!

14:21.028 --> 14:24.397
COME ON, LUCKY AMULET,
DO YOUR THING!

14:32.305 --> 14:34.841
[ROARS]

14:34.908 --> 14:36.176
I DON'T BELIEVE IT!

14:36.243 --> 14:38.678
MY LUCKY AMULET
SAVED US AGAIN!

14:38.745 --> 14:40.313
HAH!

14:41.348 --> 14:43.416
[ROARS]

14:45.152 --> 14:47.354
LIKE, HEY, HAVE YOU
COME TO SAVE US AGAIN?

14:47.420 --> 14:49.256
'CAUSE, MAN, A MAP OF
THIS PLACE WOULD BE

14:49.322 --> 14:51.024
PRETTY SWEET
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

14:51.091 --> 14:53.693
I'VE COME
FOR WHAT IS MINE!

14:53.760 --> 14:55.929
GET YOUR OWN
LUCKY AMULET!

14:55.996 --> 14:57.030
GET READY.

14:57.097 --> 14:59.032
I THINK I HEAR
SOMEONE COMING!

15:00.767 --> 15:02.035
WE GOT HIM!

15:02.102 --> 15:03.270
[THUNDERING HOOFBEATS]

15:06.839 --> 15:08.508
WE DON'T GOT HIM.

15:08.575 --> 15:11.278
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU SEE THE CENTAUR?

15:11.344 --> 15:14.781
NO. THE HOOF-MARKS
ON MY BACK ARE
A FASHION STATEMENT.

15:14.847 --> 15:16.984
OH, BLAST IT ALL!

15:17.050 --> 15:19.919
I WAS GUARDING
THE BACK EXIT
AND I MISSED IT!

15:19.987 --> 15:23.923
OH! MY LIFE'S DREAM!
WHEN WILL IT HAPPEN?

15:23.991 --> 15:25.792
WHEN?!

15:25.858 --> 15:29.929
EVER NOTICE THAT THE GOOD
MAJOR IS NEVER AROUND
WHEN THE CENTAUR APPEARS?

15:29.997 --> 15:31.131
AND YOU WOULD BE?

15:31.198 --> 15:33.433
I AM LYSANDER DEMAS,

15:33.500 --> 15:36.169
THE RIGHTFUL OWNER
OF THAT AMULET.

15:36.236 --> 15:39.206
MY LUCKY AMULET?
LIKE, NO WAY, MAN!

15:39.272 --> 15:42.275
YOU HAVE A LUCKY
AMULET, SHAGGY?

15:42.342 --> 15:46.613
LUCKY? OH, NO,
MY RUMPLED YOUNG FRIEND.

15:46.679 --> 15:48.881
THIS IS NOT LUCKY AT ALL.

15:48.948 --> 15:51.518
THIS IS THE AMULET
OF THE CENTAUR.

15:51.584 --> 15:53.186
IT DOESN'T PROTECT YOU!

15:53.253 --> 15:56.389
IN FACT,
IT ATTRACTS THE BEAST!

15:56.456 --> 15:59.826
SO THAT'S WHY THAT
MYTHOLOGICAL MONSTER'S
BEEN CHASING US!

15:59.892 --> 16:02.062
BUT IF THE AMULET
ATTRACTS THE CENTAUR,

16:02.129 --> 16:03.630
THEN WHY ARE YOU
TRYING TO GET IT?

16:03.696 --> 16:06.633
BECAUSE. YOU SEE THOSE
MARKINGS ON THE SIDE?

16:06.699 --> 16:11.238
IF YOU TAKE THIS AMULET
TO THE TEMPLE OF LIGHT
ON SANTORINI,

16:11.304 --> 16:12.905
IT WILL SHOW YOU THE WAY.

16:12.972 --> 16:14.307
THE WAY TO WHERE?

16:14.374 --> 16:17.377
TO THE LOST CITY
OF ATLANTIS.

16:26.919 --> 16:29.256
MAN, SANTORINI
SURE IS PRETTY,

16:29.322 --> 16:32.559
BUT, WHEW!
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S THIS HOT,

16:32.625 --> 16:33.893
ESPECIALLY AT NIGHT.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.395
AIEEE!

16:35.462 --> 16:38.031
LIKE, IT'S
THE CENTAUR! RUN!

16:38.098 --> 16:39.532
[ROARS]

16:41.134 --> 16:45.105
LIKE, IT'S THE OLD,
MANIAC MOPED GUY! RUN!

16:45.172 --> 16:46.639
THAT WAY!

17:39.292 --> 17:41.494
[YELLING IN GREEK]

17:43.230 --> 17:46.666
LIKE, FINE, YOU CURSED US.
WE GET IT ALREADY.

17:46.733 --> 17:50.703
HE'S NOT CURSING YOU.
HE'S TRYING TO RETURN
YOUR PURSE!

17:50.770 --> 17:51.804
All: WHAT?!

17:51.871 --> 17:53.373
WOW! MY PURSE!

17:53.440 --> 17:55.775
HERE'S THE PROBLEM.
IN MY PHRASE BOOK,

17:55.842 --> 17:58.378
"THE GREEK GODS SHALL
BRING CHAOS TO YOUR LIVES,"

17:58.445 --> 18:01.481
IS RIGHT UNDER, "I'M TRYING
TO RETURN YOUR PURSE."

18:01.548 --> 18:02.482
HEH!

18:02.549 --> 18:03.716
OOH, MY BAD.

18:03.783 --> 18:06.319
FREDDY, HOW DO YOU
SAY "THANK YOU"
IN GREEK?

18:06.386 --> 18:09.589
WHY DON'T WE ASK MR. DEMAS
TO TRANSLATE FOR US?

18:09.656 --> 18:11.924
NO. I'M AFRAID
THERE ISN'T TIME.

18:11.991 --> 18:13.826
WE HAVE TO REACH
THE TEMPLE OF LIGHT

18:13.893 --> 18:15.728
WHILE THE MOON
IS STILL OUT.

18:17.764 --> 18:19.566
OKAY. NOW WHAT?

18:19.632 --> 18:21.100
THERE!

18:23.670 --> 18:24.704
[ALL GASP]

18:24.771 --> 18:26.206
Velma: THERE!

18:26.273 --> 18:29.409
THE ENTRANCE TO
ATLANTIS MUST BE
ON THAT ISLAND.

18:31.911 --> 18:33.946
IT'S HERE, IT'S HERE!

18:34.013 --> 18:35.948
PRETTY EXCITING,
HUH, MAJOR?

18:36.015 --> 18:37.850
MAJOR?! NOW,
WHERE DID HE G--

18:37.917 --> 18:40.187
AAH!
AAH!

18:43.523 --> 18:45.024
WE'VE GOT TO
DO SOMETHING

18:45.091 --> 18:47.994
TO GET PAST THIS
RAMPAGING RODEO REJECT!

18:48.060 --> 18:52.499
WELL, HAVING MY PURSE
BACK MEANS THAT I ALSO
HAVE MY MAKEUP KIT.

18:53.533 --> 18:54.901
[CACKLES]

18:58.004 --> 19:00.440
[BELLOWS]

19:06.012 --> 19:09.849
WHOOOOH!
RAAAAH!

19:11.484 --> 19:14.254
THE CENTAUR CRASHED
THROUGH THE DOOR
TO ATLANTIS!

19:14.321 --> 19:16.856
BUT, LIKE, HEY,
THERE'S NOTHING THERE!

19:16.923 --> 19:22.094
NO WAY! WELL, I GUESS
THE MYSTERY OF ATLANTIS
WILL ALWAYS BE JUST THAT--

19:22.161 --> 19:23.196
A MYSTERY.

19:23.263 --> 19:24.631
BUT WE STILL
HAVEN'T FOUND OUT

19:24.697 --> 19:27.267
WHO'S BEHIND THE MASK
OF THIS MENACING MYTH!

19:27.334 --> 19:30.136
THAT'S EASY. THIS CAN
ONLY BE ONE PERSON--

19:30.203 --> 19:32.572
THE ONLY PERSON WHO
WAS CONVENIENTLY ABSENT

19:32.639 --> 19:34.441
WHENEVER
THE CENTAUR ATTACKED--

19:34.507 --> 19:36.943
MAJOR PORTSMOUTH.

19:37.009 --> 19:38.311
WHAT? WHO'S THIS?

19:38.378 --> 19:39.579
WE HAVEN'T EVEN MET HER!

19:39.646 --> 19:41.248
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO SHE IS!

19:41.314 --> 19:44.384
SHE'S MY ASSISTANT
SUSIE SMYTHE.

19:44.451 --> 19:46.486
AND HOW
WAS I SUPPOSED TO
KNOW THAT?

19:46.553 --> 19:50.122
NO WAY. FOUL! THIS
ONE DOES NOT COUNT.

19:50.189 --> 19:52.024
BUT WHY DID YOU DO THIS?

19:52.091 --> 19:55.695
BECAUSE THE ENTRANCE
TO ATLANTIS WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE MY DISCOVERY.

19:55.762 --> 19:58.798
I WOULD HAVE BEEN
FAMOUS IF IT WEREN'T
FOR YOU MEDDLING KIDS!

19:58.865 --> 20:03.803
WELL, I THINK YOU'LL
BE QUITE FAMOUS--WITH
THE GREEK AUTHORITIES.

20:03.870 --> 20:07.039
[PANTS] SORRY.
I WAS JUST AT THE BOAT,
GETTING MY CAMERA.

20:07.106 --> 20:09.141
DID I MISS ANY--OH!
OH, MY!

20:09.208 --> 20:11.444
I KNEW IT! I KNEW IT!

20:11.511 --> 20:14.347
IT'S REAL!
IT'S ALL REAL!

20:14.414 --> 20:18.084
[LAUGHS] OH,
THE WONDER OF IT ALL!

20:18.150 --> 20:19.185
HA HA HA HA!

20:19.252 --> 20:20.753
YOU THINK
WE SHOULD TELL HIM?

20:20.820 --> 20:21.788
NAH.
NAH.

20:21.854 --> 20:23.790
BUT THIS ISN'T FAIR.
I'M NEVER WRONG!

20:23.856 --> 20:25.525
I MEAN, SURE,
IF I'D SEEN HER,

20:25.592 --> 20:27.360
I WOULD HAVE FIGURED
IT OUT, BUT I DIDN'T!

20:27.427 --> 20:29.996
HEY, WHERE DID
SCOOBY GO?

20:30.062 --> 20:31.764
[GROWLS]

20:31.831 --> 20:33.065
SCOOBY...

20:33.132 --> 20:34.467
DOOBY...

20:34.534 --> 20:35.968
DOO!

20:36.969 --> 20:37.937
YIII!
